{"id":1294,"date":"2022-04-04T13:19:49","date_gmt":"2022-04-04T10:19:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/?p=1294"},"modified":"2022-04-04T13:19:49","modified_gmt":"2022-04-04T10:19:49","slug":"silk-roads-ross-ulbricht-announces-second-nft-collection","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/silk-roads-ross-ulbricht-announces-second-nft-collection\/","title":{"rendered":"Silk Road&#8217;s Ross Ulbricht Announces Second NFT Collection"},"content":{"rendered":"<p> <br \/>\n<\/p>\n<div itemprop=\"mainEntityOfPage\">\n<p>Early crypto adopter and contentious Web3 figure Ross Ulbricht has announced the launch of his second NFT collection. The founder of the now-defunct Silk Road platform will launch the collection from the confines of his prison cell, as he continues to serve his<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">\u00a0<\/span>double life plus 40 years sentence without parole, for his involvement in the controversial online marketplace.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>The collection is titled the \u2018Growth Collection,\u2019 and will be auctioned at the Bitcoin22 conference via <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/scarce.city\/\">Scarce.City<\/a> in Miami on April 6th-8th. It will<strong> consist of four physical oil paintings and one hand-drawn animation<\/strong> (embedded with 318 hand drawn frames), with each accompanied by a Bitcoin NFT with a Bitcoin-tokenized certificate of authenticity.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>The collection also pays homage to Bitcoin\u2019s founder Satoshi Nakamoto, whose 47th birthday is on the day before the event.<\/p>\n<p>Ulbricht has gathered much attention since first being apprehended for his operation and ownership of the website, which he was accused of enabling its users to buy and sell illegal drugs and other unlawful goods and services anonymously back in 2013. However, he insists that the collection\u2019s focus shouldn\u2019t be on his conviction, and rather, how <strong>he believes he can still make difference<\/strong> despite his seemingly indefinite incarceration.<br \/><i><br \/><\/i><i>\u201cWe can look more broadly at making the whole system just, rather than focusing just on me, that is as it should be. There is a lot of work to do\u2026All of this has brought a new spark to my life. I have direction and purpose and I feel like I can make a difference again. The more money we raise the more good we can do. I have put my heart, soul, and mind into this collection, and I am really looking forward to unveiling it to you\u201d.<\/i><\/p>\n<p>October 1st of this year will mark the 10th year of Ulbricht\u2019s highly contested prison sentence, which for many, is 10 years too long. At the time of writing, a little<strong> over 475,000 people have pledged their solidarity with the crypto pioneer<\/strong> through participating in a <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/www.change.org\/p\/clemency-for-ross-ulbricht-condemned-to-die-in-prison-for-a-website\">clemency petition<\/a>\u00a0which has been set up to fight for his freedom.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>Despite being locked away for such time, the Austin-born tech wizard was also able to launch an incredibly successful \u2018<a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/nftplazas.com\/silk-road-creator-ross-ulbricht-to-drop-first-nft-collection\/\">Ross Ulbricht Genesis Collection<\/a>\u2019 late last year, which generated $6.27 million at auction during Art Basel<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">\u00a0<\/span>Miami.<\/p>\n<p><b>Follow Ross Ulbricht &gt; <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/RealRossU\">Twitter<\/a>\u00a0<\/b><\/p>\n<p><b>Want more? Connect with NFT Plazas<\/b><\/p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/mailchi.mp\/ecadf05eb1bf\/1\">Jo